## The change
- New module constant IDLE_POLL_INTERVAL = 0.25s.
- _get_next_batch: blocks on queue.get(timeout=min(min_batch_interval,
  IDLE_POLL_INTERVAL)) for the first item (Empty -> return []), then drains the
  rest with get_nowait up to max_batch_size. Wakes immediately on arrival.
- _process_batches: removed the trailing 'if not stop: time.sleep(mbi)'. The
  blocking get is now the wait/poll. Everything else (task_done per item on all
  3 paths, exception handling, shutdown drain+exit check) unchanged.

